A true Winter color palette is full of cool based jewel-tones like ruby red, sapphire blue, and emerald green. Winter types also get such classic neutrals ‚Äì they look beautiful in black, crisp white, and navy to name a few. A true Winter palette is full of colors that lean crisp, cool, and highly saturated. As a color season Winter, you look amazing in high contrast. That means the colors you wear are more different from each other than they are similar. Here is a visual representation of high contrast versus low contrast.
High Contrast outfit ‚Äì black, white, red
Low contrast outfit ‚Äì shades of blue
