289,https://yourcolorguru.com/save-500-this-year-by-getting-your-colors-done/,"Have you ever heard that most people only wear 20% of what is in their closet? It‚Äôs true! Don‚Äôt you find yourself grabbing the same stuff over and over again?
Meanwhile, you‚Äôre ignoring all of these clothes that you spent good money on. You try it on, you take it back off. It just doesn‚Äôt feel right. Why don‚Äôt you want to wear those clothes? You aren‚Äôt even sure.
I‚Äôm speaking from personal experience here. For the longest time, my cluttered closet left me frustrated. I wasn‚Äôt wearing more than half of my clothes, so why did I buy them in the first place? I felt guilty for the money I‚Äôd wasted, but I couldn‚Äôt help it, I did not want to wear those clothes!
Here‚Äôs the thing. No one teaches us how to buy what is actually right for us, clothing-wise. Most women are taught to impulse shop. I know I was. Go the the clothing store, browse around, and buy what you like in the moment. 2 weeks later, you try and wear it‚Ä¶and hmmm‚Ä¶you don‚Äôt really like it anymore. What happened? Impulse buy regret strikes again.
